12/1/99
  Demo2_1: Progress refresh simulation died after statmux received
  frame 14495 (about 8 mins).  Input file location 522409512.

  Demo2_2: Messy splice successfully finished.

  Demo3_1: Rerun progressive refresh simulation with file offset of 514057424.


12/2/99
  Trying to fix the Dev/Hw source directory.
  Added endPicStat in chanInfo to point to the last picture before turning off
  a channel.  This simplifies the Output Task.

  Progressive refresh simulation die again, at roughly the same age.
  Output file size: 260571136 or 290267136
  Output frames: 14644 or 16299
  Guess: output file size is roughly 2^32/2/8.  Seems like a Int32 bit counter
         may have wrap around!
  Notice that there is no such problem if progress refresh flag is turned off!


  Testing reliability of dpi123.fls
    - Audio careless bug fixed.
    - Harmonic Lightway RC bug fixed.


  - New spPicStat, sentPicStat, endPicStat and muxPicStat convention
    spPicStat is initially set to NULL at start up.
    When a new picture is passed to switcher, spPicStat will be updated
    to point to this picture.
    spPicStat will remain non NULL until the channel is closed down.

    muxPicStat is initially set to NULL at start up.
    When a new picture is passed to switcher, muxPicStat will be set
    to this picture if muxPicStat is NULL.
    After the last picture in Switcher has been passed or dropped
    (muxPicStat==spPicStat), muxPicStat is set to NULL.

    When a channel is to be turned off, endPicStat will be set to point to
    the last picture before turned off.

    outPicStat is updated by the outputTask and points to the last picture
    sent out by output task.


12/3/99
  Overnight result of dpi123.fls:
    Stopped switching after force switch, which happens in about 30 minutes.

  A bug found in procSwitchTimeout().  Need to set endPicStat.
  Or in case output Task has already sent out the last picture,
  signal the spliceControl Task directly. 
  Bug fixed by adding outPicStat in ChanInfo.

  Noticed that whenever there are skip pictures, the free TP level drops.
  Also pidChansHandle's pidQue counter gets negative!
  Bug fixed in rateConvPic() in rateconv.c.

  Study of progressive refresh simulation results show that the segmantation
  problem may be due to the outage of free PidBuf.  The free PidBuf level
  graduately drops.  May have pidBuf leak when inserting I picture!

  A temporary solution is to increase the PidBuf count by roughly 5 times so
  hopefully the simulation can be done before the buffers run out.

  With the new picStat convention, we may not need the FINISHING chan mode!


